# sample  register  data
# Channel 0, all-carrier algorithm at feedback 0, one distinct DT1/DT2 pair
# per operator so every fine-detune sign and coarse-detune value grades as a
# separate phase rate. KC $44 (block 4, note 4) puts the gap-removed position
# at 192: DT2 values 1 and 2 stay inside the 768-entry table row while
# DT2 3 (+608) crosses it and exercises the single-overflow block adjust.
# Raw slots: M1 DT1=+1 DT2=0, M2 DT1=-1 DT2=1, C1 DT1=+3 DT2=2,
# C2 DT1=0 DT2=3; all multipliers 1.
